fields.name: resourceType
fields.descr: "This is a Sequence resource"

fields.name: identifier
fields.descr: "A unique identifier for this particular sequence instance. This is a FHIR-defined id."

fields.name: type
fields.descr: "Amino Acid Sequence/ DNA Sequence / RNA Sequence."

fields.name: _type
fields.descr: "Extensions for type"

fields.name: coordinateSystem
fields.descr: "Whether the sequence is numbered starting at 0 (0-based numbering or coordinates, inclusive start, exclusive end) or starting at 1 (1-based numbering, inclusive start and inclusive end)."

fields.name: _coordinateSystem
fields.descr: "Extensions for coordinateSystem"

fields.name: patient
fields.descr: "The patient whose sequencing results are described by this resource."

fields.name: specimen
fields.descr: "Specimen used for sequencing."

fields.name: device
fields.descr: "The method for sequencing, for example, chip information."

fields.name: performer
fields.descr: "The organization or lab that should be responsible for this result."

fields.name: quantity
fields.descr: "The number of copies of the seqeunce of interest. (RNASeq)."

fields.name: referenceSeq
fields.descr: "A sequence that is used as a reference to describe variants that are present in a sequence analyzed."

fields.name: variant
fields.descr: "The definition of variant here originates from Sequence ontology ([variant_of](http://www.sequenceontology.org/browser/current_svn/term/variant_of)). This element can represent amino acid or nucleic sequence change(including insertion,deletion,SNP,etc.)  It can represent some complex mutation or segment variation with the assist of CIGAR string."

fields.name: observedSeq
fields.descr: "Sequence that was observed. It is the result marked by referenceSeq along with variant records on referenceSeq. This shall starts from referenceSeq.windowStart and end by referenceSeq.windowEnd."

fields.name: _observedSeq
fields.descr: "Extensions for observedSeq"

fields.name: quality
fields.descr: "An experimental feature attribute that defines the quality of the feature in a quantitative way, such as a phred quality score ([SO:0001686](http://www.sequenceontology.org/browser/current_svn/term/SO:0001686))."

fields.name: readCoverage
fields.descr: "Coverage (read depth or depth) is the average number of reads representing a given nucleotide in the reconstructed sequence."

fields.name: _readCoverage
fields.descr: "Extensions for readCoverage"

fields.name: repository
fields.descr: "Configurations of the external repository. The repository shall store target's observedSeq or records related with target's observedSeq."

fields.name: pointer
fields.descr: "Pointer to next atomic sequence which at most contains one variant."
